SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Museum Exhibition: 'the halls of a changing sea' 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50392821326668
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/the-halls-of-a-changing-sea
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Workshops and Training,Community Events,Exhib
 itions
DESCRIPTION:Join Raleigh-based artist Isabel Lu for Medicine\, Told & Retol
 d: WATER\, an art workshop that will center on themes related to arts and w
 ellness and the exhibition The House of Ideas: Plants in Art. The exhibitio
 n is on display at the Gregg Museum of Art & Design through May 2026.  It f
 eatures objects from the Gregg's collection that depict the roles of plants
  from nourishment and communal living to the scientific study of human heal
 th. The exhibition includes a relaxing room for botanical sketching and a s
 elf-guided tour of the museum’s garden.\n\nLu's workshop will provide an op
 portunity for participants to learn\, relearn and creatively explore their 
 relationships to plants\, medicine and body with guidance from Chinese medi
 cine. Framed under the five elements in Chinese medicine – fire\, earth\, m
 etal\, water and wood – the workshop will explore how we can nourish oursel
 ves with plants and the element of water.  Through discussion\, herbalism a
 nd reflection\, participants will find space to move and adapt through wint
 er\, cold and fear.\n\nLu\, who has a Master of Public Health\, is a regist
 ered dietitian and a researcher whose work unpacks rigid\, violent and bina
 ry concepts of health and medicine through Western and Eastern perspectives
 .\n\nThe workshop is free and open to the public\, but registration is requ
 ired.
DTEND:20260217T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215952Z
DTSTART:20260217T193000Z
GEO:35.784762;-78.661636
LOCATION:Gregg Museum of Art & Design\, Sun Room 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Medicine\, Told & Retold: WATER
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51966540840610
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/medicine-told-retold-water
END:VEVENT
