BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Community Events,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:The Crafts Center and the Gregg Museum of Art & Design are hono
 red to host Jaki Shelton Green for a panel discussion followed by a Q&A in 
 conjunction with the exhibition WORDS = POWER. Green will have a book signi
 ng that will include various publications and CDs for sale.\n\nGreen is the
  first African American and third woman to serve as the North Carolina poet
  laureate. When former Gov. Roy Cooper appointed her in 2018\, he stated th
 at “Jaki Shelton Green brings a deep appreciation of our state’s diverse co
 mmunities to her role as an ambassador of North Carolina literature. Jaki’s
  appointment is a wonderful new chapter in North Carolina’s rich literary h
 istory.”\n\nASL interpreters and CART captions will be available. For addit
 ional accommodation requests\, please contact Tamara Velasco at tgvelasc@nc
 su.edu by February 5. We will do our best to honor requests made after this
  deadline. \n\nThis event is free\, but registration is required.
DTEND:20260220T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215952Z
DTSTART:20260219T230000Z
GEO:35.784762;-78.661636
LOCATION:Gregg Museum of Art & Design
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:An Evening with NC Poet Laureate Jaki Shelton Green
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50382991831341
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/talk-with-jaki-shelton-green
END:VEVENT
